sentences: She was the daughter of James Cooksey Culwick (1875–1907), professor of music, and Mary Jane (née Richardson), his second wife.
Her father held a number of positions as organist in Dublin, finally at Chapel Royal, Dublin Castle where he remained until his death in 1907.
During World War I the choir was exclusively female, but in 1919 it was back at full strength and flourishing.
In 1927, the choir won a prize at the Welsh Eisteddfod at Holyhead.
